=head1 DESCRIPTION

Contains configurations to override a prompt template in one part of an
agent sequence. For more information, see Advanced prompts
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/bedrock/latest/userguide/advanced-prompts.html).

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 AdditionalModelRequestFields => L<Paws::BedrockAgent::Document>

If the Converse or ConverseStream operations support the model,
C<additionalModelRequestFields> contains additional inference
parameters, beyond the base set of inference parameters in the
C<inferenceConfiguration> field.

For more information, see I<Inference request parameters and response
fields for foundation models> in the Amazon Bedrock user guide.


=head2 BasePromptTemplate => Str

Defines the prompt template with which to replace the default prompt
template. You can use placeholder variables in the base prompt template
to customize the prompt. For more information, see Prompt template
placeholder variables
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/bedrock/latest/userguide/prompt-placeholders.html).
For more information, see Configure the prompt templates
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/bedrock/latest/userguide/advanced-prompts-configure.html).


=head2 FoundationModel => Str

The agent's foundation model.


=head2 InferenceConfiguration => L<Paws::BedrockAgent::InferenceConfiguration>

Contains inference parameters to use when the agent invokes a
foundation model in the part of the agent sequence defined by the
C<promptType>. For more information, see Inference parameters for
foundation models
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/bedrock/latest/userguide/model-parameters.html).


=head2 ParserMode => Str

Specifies whether to override the default parser Lambda function when
parsing the raw foundation model output in the part of the agent
sequence defined by the C<promptType>. If you set the field as
C<OVERRIDDEN>, the C<overrideLambda> field in the
PromptOverrideConfiguration
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/bedrock/latest/APIReference/API_agent_PromptOverrideConfiguration.html)
must be specified with the ARN of a Lambda function.


=head2 PromptCreationMode => Str

Specifies whether to override the default prompt template for this
C<promptType>. Set this value to C<OVERRIDDEN> to use the prompt that
you provide in the C<basePromptTemplate>. If you leave it as
C<DEFAULT>, the agent uses a default prompt template.


=head2 PromptState => Str

Specifies whether to allow the agent to carry out the step specified in
the C<promptType>. If you set this value to C<DISABLED>, the agent
skips that step. The default state for each C<promptType> is as
follows.

=over

=item *

C<PRE_PROCESSING> E<ndash> C<ENABLED>

=item *

C<ORCHESTRATION> E<ndash> C<ENABLED>

=item *

C<KNOWLEDGE_BASE_RESPONSE_GENERATION> E<ndash> C<ENABLED>

=item *

C<POST_PROCESSING> E<ndash> C<DISABLED>

=back



=head2 PromptType => Str

The step in the agent sequence that this prompt configuration applies
to.



